&lt;p&gt;At DigitalOcean, we simplify the cloud so builders can change the world. To do that, we need managers who are empowered, informed, and human-centric. This isn&#39;t a &quot;behind-the-scenes&quot; HR role. We are looking for a Manager Success Partner who acts as the expert at the elbow—a thinking partner who doesn&#39;t just process people&#39;s problems but anticipates them. If you are someone who loves to dive into the &quot;people cost&quot; of business decisions, uses AI to automate the mundane, and builds the kind of credibility where you are the first call a manager makes, this is your next career chapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Manager Success Partner to be the go-to thinking partner for front-line and mid-level managers. Reporting to the Director, People Business Partners, you will bridge the gap between business strategy and daily team dynamics. You will be responsible for building a deep understanding of our business model to ensure our people strategy drives actual growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the &quot;Expert at the Elbow&quot; for managers, coaching them through difficult conversations and team dynamics so they show up better for their teams every day. Help empower mid-level managers to make high-quality, consistent people decisions, thereby protecting the company’s culture and legal standing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle &quot;Complex Execution.&quot; These are tasks that require judgment and coaching, business understanding, contextual knowledge and experience, not just following a checklist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Data-Informed Decisions by using HRIS (Workday) to surface trends in turnover and headcount, asking the &quot;right&quot; questions about the numbers rather than just passing them along.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce Data Hygiene as a non-negotiable to maintain a single source of truth, guiding managers to self-service tools and chatbots to ensure reliable, instant, and automated insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate Engagement Data into Action by partnering with managers to make sense of team feedback and turning it into a living roadmap rather than just a static slide.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve Complex Employee Relations (ER) situations with consistency and care, building long-term credibility as a confidant who helps managers prepare for hard situations before they happen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Execution of People Cycles (Performance, Comp, Surveys) with obsessive follow-through, keeping stakeholders informed and FAQs ready before they are even asked.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI and Digital Tools to reduce time spent on administrative drafting and scheduling, intentionally shifting your energy toward high-impact manager conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Add&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Breadth: 5+ years of HR experience with a focus on business partnership. You are a Workday power-user who is comfortable with descriptive data reporting and has a growing appetite for using AI to streamline HR workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business Acumen: A working knowled

